Reasoning: The paper introduces a new class of automata on infinite trees and discusses their decidability. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic (cs.LO) or Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions algorithms for the satisfiability of a probabilistic temporal logic, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, as automata are often used in the study of machine learning algorithms.
